parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coils can cause the engine to stall or misfire, leading to a loss of power and potential accidents, especially when driving on highways. This issue can also cause financial hardship due to the high cost of replacement.
symptoms: Engine stalling
misfiring
rough idling
loss of power
check engine light illumination
sudden failure of ignition coils
repeated replacement of ignition coils.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, compromising the safety of vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
airbag warning light is illuminated
rattling noise from the passenger side airbag area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunction of the airbag system can lead to false warnings, failure to deploy airbags in a crash, or unintended airbag deployment, which can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Airbag warning light is illuminated
rattling noise from the passenger side airbag area
airbag recall notice received but unable to verify recall status.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly without warning
the gas pedal becomes slack
the vehicle continues to rev even when in park
the vehicle bucks and hesitates when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition coil failure can cause the vehicle to hesitate, buck, and lose power, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates and bucks when accelerating
the vehicle will not accelerate past a certain speed
the check engine light does not come on despite the problem.
